      "content": "While waiting a few hours might seem like a simple fix, the enzymes in grapefruit juice can have lingering effects in your digestive system. To truly ensure your atorvastatin is working correctly and safely, the best course of action is to separate them by more than just a few hours, ideally by having the juice at a completely different time of day. If fatigue is a concern, you should discuss it with your doctor, as it could be a sign that your current dosage needs a slight adjustment.",
